org.microtitan.diffusive.diffuser.restful

Class DiffuserSignature

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.microtitan.diffusive.diffuser.restful.DiffuserSignature
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.freezedry.persistence.copyable.Copyable<DiffuserSignature>

    public class DiffuserSignature
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.freezedry.persistence.copyable.Copyable<DiffuserSignature>
    Encapsulates the key used to identify a Diffuser for a specific method. The Diffuser ID is based on:
    • the name of the Class that contains the diffused method
    • the name of the method
    • a list of the class names for each of the arguments passed to the method
    • the Class name of the return type
    The Diffuser ID is constructed as follows:

    class:method(argument1,argument2,argument3,...,argumentN)-returnType

    where the "class" is the fully qualified class name; the method is the name of the method; the arguments are all the fully qualified class names of the argument; and the returnType is the fully qualified class name of the return type (which could be void.class. The DiffuserSignature can be instantiated through the constructors, or preferably, through one of the four create(...) methods, or the parse(String) method. The DiffuserSignature objects are immutable.

    Author:
    Robert Philipp

      • parse

        Parses the specified diffuser ID string into a DiffuserSignature object. The Diffuser ID is constructed as follows:

        class:method(argument1,argument2,argument3,...,argumentN)-returnType
